  "id": "1f8803c2-a096-5d42-bf5c-aa8c8071ea48",
  "slug": "asian-style-spare-ribs",
  "name": "Asian Style Spare Ribs",
  "recipe_type": "main",
  "brief_description": "I enjoy eating spare ribs to the point that I don't mind how messy my hands are while indulging every bite. This recipe post is all about Asian Style Spare Ribs. It is a simple spare ribs dish that is full of flavor. I also liked how the meat got really tender.",
  "cuisine": "asian",
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Combine soy sauce, molasses, lime juice, garlic powder, and ground black pepper in a bowl. Stir until well blended."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Put the sliced pork spare ribs in a resealable bag. Pour-in the soy sauce mixture. Let the air out, then seal the bag. Place it inside the refrigerator and marinate overnight."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Preheat oven to 350F."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Line a parchment paper or aluminum foil on an oval roaster (use the roaster with cover). Arrange the marinated pork spare ribs on top. Brush the spare ribs with hoisin sauce."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Cover the roaster and roast the ribs for 50 to 60 minutes."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Arrange the ribs in a serving plate. Brush more Hoisin sauce, if preferred. Sprinkle sesame seeds all over the ribs."
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "Serve with homemade French fries or enjoy it with white rice. Share and enjoy."
    }
  ],
  "servings": 6,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 60,
  "preparation_time_minutes": 10,
